What this gives you

A live dashboard at http://localhost:8000 where you paste XTSG syntax and execute.

Results show the events plus the Fedorian rollup signature (cryptographic binding).

The WebSocket endpoint is scaffolded for future live streaming of events.


If you want, I can next add:

A force-directed graph view of seals/events (D3.js).

A /api/run/file endpoint to run .xtsg or .adm files from disk.

A GitHub Actions job that boots this dashboard on PR previews (e.g., via Docker).


